              },
              "free_text": [
                " Measurement performed at the",
                "Los Alamos Neutron Science Center at the WNR-15L",
                "beam line at LANSCE where an 800-MeV pulsed proton beam",
                "impacts on spallation target."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "92-U-235",
                "field_identifier": "ENR",
                "value": 0.9991
              },
              "free_text": [
                " 112 mg of enriched 235U deposited",
                "on both sides of ten plates in parallel-plate avalanche",
                "chamber.The diameter of each 235U deposit was 4 cm,",
                "resulting in an area of approximately 12.6 cm2 on each",
                "plate. The plates are separated by approximately 1 cm."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "SPALL"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " A white photon source created by the high-",
                "energy spallation photons arriving ahead of the neutron",
                "beam at the Los Alamos Neutron Science Center (LANSCE)",
                "was used as photon source."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PPAC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Parallel-plate avalanche chamber containing 10",
                "plates with deposited target 235U was used for fission",
                "fragments detection"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Array of 16 organic liquid scintillation",
                "detectors (EJ309) was used. Each detector was 7.62 cm",
                "in diameter and 5.08-cm thick. The detectors were",
                "placed approximately 22 cm away from the center of the",
                "fission chamber, arranged on two rings, each holding",
                "eight detectors with a total azimuthal angular coverage",
                "of approximately 270deg. A detection threshold of",
                "40 keVee (approximately 0.5 MeV of deposited proton-",
                "recoil energy) was applied.",
                "A Cf252 source was used for detector efficiency",
                "calibration."
              ]
            }
          ],
